# backend/LEAN_AGENT_SYSTEM.md

# Lean Agent System: The Expert Approach

## Philosophy: Less Tools, More Data

Instead of complex multi-agent orchestration, SalesInject uses:

1. **Hermes**: Stateless data capture & validation layer
2. **Direct Database**: Minimal intermediate processing
3. **Telegram Bot**: Primary user interaction channel
4. **Simple Job Queue**: When jobs are needed

This is the approach used by successful platforms:
- **OpenAI Swarm**: Lightweight agent handoff
- **Anthropic Models API**: Direct prompt-based communication
- **Pydantic AI**: Minimal state management

## Architecture

```
Landing Page
    ↓
Onboarding (Hermes captures data)
    ↓
Database (Store user profile)
    ↓
Telegram Bot (Primary interface)
    ↓
User Actions (Create offers, claim offers, message)
    ↓
Jobs (Only when needed: content gen, notifications)
```

## No Complex Agents—Just Three Data Flows

### 1. Brand Flow
- Brand signs up → Profile created in DB
- Brand logs into Telegram bot
- Brand creates campaign/offer
- System matches influencers via simple SQL query
- Direct messaging between brand ↔ influencer

### 2. Influencer Flow
- Influencer signs up → Avatar profile created
- Influencer logs into Telegram bot
- Influencer views map of available offers (DeckGL frontend)
- Influencer claims offer → Proof submission
- Influencer earns money

### 3. Communication Flow
- Brand → Influencer: "Hi, I have a product"
- Influencer → Brand: "I'm interested"
- Simple message table in DB
- No agent mediation needed

## Tools Used (Minimal)

| Tool | Purpose | Complexity |
|------|---------|-----------|
| Hermes | Data capture from forms | 1/10 |
| OpenRouter LLM | Content generation (on demand) | 2/10 |
| Telegram Bot | User interface | 3/10 |
| DeckGL | Map visualization | 4/10 |
| Celery | Async tasks (optional) | 2/10 |
| PostgreSQL | Data storage | 2/10 |

**Total System Complexity: 3/10**

## What NOT to Use

❌ Complex agent frameworks (Crew AI, AutoGen, etc.)
❌ Multi-layer memory systems
❌ Tool registries with 20+ tools
❌ State machines for every workflow
❌ Event buses for simple operations

## Data Model (Minimal)

```
Users
  ├── id (UUID)
  ├── telegram_id (linked during onboarding)
  ├── role (brand or influencer)
  ├── metadata (JSONB—flexible schema)
  └── created_at

Products (Brand-created)
  ├── id, brand_id, name, price

Campaigns (Brand-created)
  ├── id, brand_id, title, budget, requirements

Offers (Brand-created, location-based)
  ├── id, campaign_id, lat, lon, bounty, promo_code

OfferClaims (Influencer claims)
  ├── id, offer_id, influencer_id, status, proof_url

Messages (Direct chat)
  ├── id, sender_id, recipient_id, content, is_read

Agents (Lightweight)
  ├── id, user_id, type (avatar), config (JSONB)
  └── Only created after full onboarding
```

## Onboarding Process (3 Steps)

1. **Landing Page** → Click "START NOW"
2. **Signup Form** → Choose role + basic info
   - Brand: Company name, industry, budget
   - Influencer: Display name, bio, social links
3. **Telegram Join** → Deep link starts bot conversation

All data flows through Hermes endpoints before DB storage.

## API Surface (Minimal)

```
POST   /onboarding/api/onboard               # Capture initial data
POST   /onboarding/api/brand/profile         # Complete brand profile
POST   /onboarding/api/influencer/avatar     # Complete influencer avatar
GET    /onboarding/api/user/{user_id}/summary  # Verify before Telegram
GET    /onboarding/telegram/{user_id}        # Redirect to bot

POST   /api/v1/campaigns                     # Brand creates campaign
POST   /api/v1/offers                        # Brand creates offer
GET    /api/v1/offers?lat=X&lon=Y           # Influencer discovers offers
POST   /api/v1/offers/{id}/claim            # Influencer claims offer
POST   /api/v1/messages                      # Send message
GET    /api/v1/messages/{user_id}           # Get messages
```

## Telegram Bot Commands

```
/start                                       # Initialize/join
/campaigns (for brands)                     # Create campaign
/offers (for influencers)                   # View offers
/message @user                              # Send message
/profile                                    # View/edit profile
/earnings (for influencers)                 # View earnings
```

## When to Use Celery Jobs

Only for:
1. **Async notifications** → Send Telegram/email
2. **Content generation** → Call OpenRouter LLM
3. **Periodic tasks** → Clean up expired offers
4. **Heavy computation** → Image processing, etc.

❌ NOT for simple database operations
❌ NOT for message routing
❌ NOT for user authentication

## Success Metrics

- Onboarding: < 2 minutes per user
- Message delivery: < 1 second
- Offer discovery: < 500ms
- System maintenance: 1 person
- Code complexity: < 10K lines Python

## Future Enhancements (Only if needed)

1. AI recommendation engine (suggest offers for influencers)
2. Content generation workflow (assist in creating hooks)
3. Reputation/scoring system
4. Multi-language support

But start with this minimal version first.
